THE funeral details for award-winning actor and TV presenter Akhumzi Jezile (29) have been confirmed. The family said a memorial service will be held tomorrow at Rhema Bible Church in Randburg, Joburg, at 2pm. The funeral service will also be held at the church, on Saturday at 9am. Akhumzi will be laid to rest at Westpark Cemetery. Akhumzi was killed in a horrific car accident in Queenstown, Eastern Cape, with four other passengers. The crash also claimed the lives of singer and actor Siyasanga Kobese, actor Thobani Mseleni and IT specialist at Urban Brew Studios, Skhumbuzo Mbuthuma. The identity of the fifth passenger had not been released at the time of going to print.